WEBVTT

00:01:27.391 --> 00:01:30.475
That's because you have to know
how to put the words together.

00:01:30.499 --> 00:01:33.210
That is, a real language has grammar.

00:01:33.234 --> 00:01:34.692
Elvish does.

00:01:34.716 --> 00:01:38.182
In English, to make a verb past,
you add an "-ed."

00:01:38.206 --> 00:01:39.688
Wash, washed.

00:01:39.712 --> 00:01:42.224
In Elvish, "wash" is "allu"

00:01:42.248 --> 00:01:44.315
and "washed" is "allune."

00:01:45.382 --> 00:01:47.822
Real languages also change over time.

00:01:47.846 --> 00:01:49.818
There's no such thing as a language

00:01:49.842 --> 00:01:52.747
that's the same today
as it was a thousand years ago.

00:01:52.771 --> 00:01:55.417
As people speak, they drift
into new habits,

00:01:55.441 --> 00:01:56.632
shed old ones,

00:01:56.656 --> 00:01:58.733
make mistakes, and get creative.

